A paper cup.
It was only a paper cup.
Not even a nice paper cup.
Not a colorful paper cup.
It was an ordinary paper cup, used to hold coffee or water or other drinks.
And it was special to me.
I remember the first time I met the paper cup.
It was a long time ago.
It was a time when I was very young.
I was only six years old.
I had just moved into a new house.
It was the first time I had ever moved.
I didn’t know anyone.
I was very scared.
But my mom told me not to worry.
She said I would make new friends.
I didn’t know what that meant.
I was just a little boy.
I was very sad.
One day, a girl came to my house.
She was very pretty.
She said she was my friend.
I was very happy.
I didn’t know what to do.
I didn’t know what to say.
But I smiled at her.
And she smiled back at me.
I wanted to play with her.
I wanted to talk to her.
But I didn’t know how.
Then the girl gave me a paper cup.
She said it was my cup.
She said it was my very own cup.
She said it was just for me.
I was very happy.
I didn’t know why.
But I felt very happy.
Then the girl said, “Do you want to play with me?”
I said, “Yes.”
She said, “What do you want to play?”
I said, “I want to play with the paper cup.”
